# Security Policy — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Reporting Vulnerabilities
Report security issues privately via GitHub Security Advisories.

## Security Measures
- No credentials stored in code or repository
- Config file permissions: 600
- Secrets resolved from config file or environment variables
- All external input validated
- Dependencies pinned and audited
- Docker container runs as non-root

## Credential Resolution
Config file (`~/.config/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/config.toml`) → Environment variables

## Logging
All logs go to stderr. stdout is reserved for MCP protocol.
Security-relevant events are logged at WARN or ERROR level.
